{"by":"ai_critic","id":47779512,"kids":[47779706],"parent":47778758,"text":"I think that this is an interesting attempt at taxonomy, but it&#x27;s a bit on the magical thinking end (and I say this as somebody that does a good amount of what&#x27;s described as the <i>incanter</i> role). It&#x27;s a combination of the author&#x27;s previous witchy aesthetic (see his excellent &quot;&lt;x&gt;ing the technical interview&quot; series) and progressive labor politics (which are asymptotically doomed in the current automation push).<p>The biggest failure of imagination, I think, is the assumption we&#x27;d use humans for most (or *any) of these jobs--for example, the work of the haruspex is better left to an LLM that can process the myriad of internal states (this is the mechanical interpretation field).","time":1776263381,"type":"comment"}